author: Julia O'Donoghue, NOLA.com | The Times-Picayune
title: Missed the last Louisiana governor debate? TV station has it on demand
text:
WWL-TV has made the final Louisiana gubernatorial debate available online at its website .
The event was held on Wednesday night (Oct. 21) at LSU in Baton Rouge. Public Service Commissioner Scott Angelle, Lt. Gov. Jay Dardenne and state Rep. John Bel Edwards participated. U.S. Sen. David Vitter was not in attendance.
The hour-long debate has been split up into three videos. You can watch them here or below.
